             was again indicted for that he, on the <rs id="t18290409-320-cd1806" type="crimeDate">5th of September</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-320-off1807 t18290409-320-cd1806"></join>, at St. Mary, Matfelon, alias Whitehapel, having in his custody and possession a certain bill of exchange, which is as follows:</p>
               <p>Â£18: 5: 6 London, September 5, 1828.</p>
               <p>Four months after date. pay to my order Eighteen Pounds, Five Shillings, and Sixpence. Value received, R. H. GREEN. To Mr. 
